The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and their application to artificial intelligence. Specifically, it focuses on life-long learning and off-policy learning, which are topics that fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of these algorithms on a physical robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of value functions, which are commonly used in control systems (cs.SY), and the use of tile coding, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CV.
